  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a dim, greenish interior with a close view of an ornate dark door handle against a paneled door. Light leaks from beyond the door, creating a shadowy, suspenseful atmosphere. Tall glass-paned doors or windows with sheer curtains fill the room, their pale green curtains glowing softly. A dark figure in a brimmed hat appears through the curtains and doorway, moving into the space. The person is mostly a silhouette, with a bright circular light shining from chest height or hand level, like a flashlight, flaring toward the viewer and obscuring details of the face.\n\nInside the dark room, a framed portrait hangs on the wall. The painting appears to show an elegantly dressed woman, warmly lit in pink and amber tones, set in an ornate frame. The hat-wearing figure passes close to the portrait, still mostly in shadow, as if searching or prowling through a grand, old-fashioned interior.\n\nA close view follows of a hand turning or gripping a polished door handle near a round decorative plate. The image is dark and intimate, emphasizing the hand and hardware. Then the scene moves to a woman’s bare upper chest and collarbone area. She wears a black or very dark, glittering spaghetti-strap dress. A small perfume applicator or bottle is held near her skin, and a narrow shiny streak of liquid is drawn downward on the center of her chest, catching the light as a vertical glimmer.\n\nThe woman is then seen from the front in low, dramatic lighting. She appears to be an adult woman with fair skin, shoulder-length wavy blonde hair, dark eye makeup, and a serious, composed expression. She wears the same shimmering, low-cut evening dress with thin straps. She looks forward, then slightly to the side, her face calm and enigmatic, with windows and dark interior shapes behind her.\n\nA door opens only a narrow crack, and the woman’s face appears in the gap. At first only part of her forehead and one eye are visible; then more of her face comes into view. She peers through the partly opened door with a steady, unreadable expression, framed tightly by the door and doorjamb.\n\nThe image shifts to three adult men in formal evening wear, all in black tuxedos with white shirts and black bow ties. They stand together near a window or doorway, looking toward something offscreen. One blond man stands in front at left, a dark-haired man is behind him in the center, and a brown-haired man is at right in profile before turning more toward the same direction. Their faces look tense, surprised, or transfixed, and they remain grouped closely, as if reacting to the woman’s entrance or presence.\n\nThe woman then stands alone on an upper landing or balcony in a grand interior. A white door is behind her, deep red walls flank the doorway, and a wall sconce glows on the left. A framed picture hangs on the right wall. A dark railing with white balusters runs across the foreground. She faces forward in the shimmering green-gold evening dress, standing upright and still. She lowers one arm to the railing and then places her other hand on her hip, adopting a poised, confident stance.\n\nFinally, the product appears as a display. On the right is a tall, bright emerald-green perfume bottle with a slim cap, standing upright on a reflective surface. To its left are decorative objects, including a soft purple-toned shape and a small cluster of pale flowers or beads. Large white on-screen text reads “Emeraude by Coty,” identifying the perfume.",
